[+1170] Seattle cartoonist: May 22 is 'Everybody Draw Mohammed Day'
item.description: As a snarky response to Muslim bloggers who "warned" Comedy Central about an episode of South Park showing the Prophet Mohammed wearing a bear suit, one Seattle cartoonist, who calls laughter her form of "prayer," is asking artists all over the world to create depictions of Mohammed on May 20, then submit the images to a Facebook page she set up.

[+913] Homeless 'Hero' Ignored While Dying on NYC Street (w/video)
item.description: A heroic homeless man, stabbed after saving a Queens woman from a knife-wielding attacker, lay dying in a pool of blood for more than an hour as nearly 25 people indifferently strolled past him.

item.title: [+907] Stephen Hawking: alien life is out there, scientist warns
item.description: Stephen Hawking has suggested that aliens almost certainly exist but has warned humanity not to try to contact them.

item.title: [+760] Steve Wozniak: Apple Security, Employee Firing, Gray Powell
item.description: During last week's iPhone leak saga, Steve Wozniak, co-founder of Apple, reached out to us with a story: The morning of the iPad launch, an engineer showed Woz an iPad for two minutes. For this he was fired. It's a story that paints Apple as many people already see the company: ruthlessly secretive, and even vindictive.

item.title: [+733] Maybe legalizing drugs would be best tactic
item.description: A colloquial definition of insanity is “doing the same thing over and over again, expecting a different result.” We’ve been throwing billions upon billions of dollars and hundreds of law enforcement and military lives at the drug problem for decades. At what point to do we take a breath and rethink our strategy?

item.title: [+699] Concert Pianist Plays iPad Onstage (video)
item.description: In concert in San Francisco, Lang Lang played 'Flight of the Bumblebee' using the Magic Piano iPad app. He even let a bemused conductor, who cursorily resembled a relative of Ben Kingsley and Dr. Evil, share in the experience.

item.title: [+683] Launch of Secret US Space Ship Masks Even More Secret Launch
item.description: Somewhere above earth is America’s latest spaceship, a 30ft craft so classified that the Pentagon will not divulge its mission nor how much it cost to build.

item.title: [+655] Conan O'Brien & Jim Carrey Perform Superman LIVE (VID)
item.description: Last night Conan O’Brien continued his “Legally Prohibited From Being Funny On Television Tour” in Los Angeles, California at the Gibson Amphitheater. He was accompanied by a special guest, the one and only Jim Carrey. Jim sauntered onstage dressed as Superman to help Conan perform Five For Fighting’s Superman (It’s Not Easy).
